abstract: Pentagon says it has repatriated Guantanamo Bay detainee Abdul Rahman Shalabi, Saudi who was likely onetime bodyguard for Osama bin Laden; remaining detainee population is now 114.
lead_paragraph: The United States held the man as a wartime prisoner for more than 13 years, government files show. President Obama seeks to close the wartime prison by the time he leaves office.

headline.main: Saudi Held at Guantánamo Is Repatriated, Reducing Number of Detainees to 114
